$ SAS: restricted options
@ restricted options

→ Companies-Products/SAS/programming/options[Options] can be restricted. Restricted options cannot be changed by a user.
An option can be restricted globally, by group and by user.

Options are restricted in the following files with the normal → Companies-Products/SAS/files/configuration[config file] format:
  • Global restrictions: → Linux/fhs/usr/local/SAS/SASFoundation/9_x/misc/rstropts/rsasv9_cfg
  • Group restricitons: → Linux/fhs/usr/local/SAS/SASFoundation/9_x/misc/rstropts/groups/group-name_rsasv9_cfg
  • User restrictions: → Linux/fhs/usr/local/SAS/SASFoundation/9_x/misc/rstropts/users/user-id_rsav9_cfg

{ Querying restricted options

  Restricted options can be queried with → Companies-Products/SAS/programming/proc/options[`proc options`]:
code {
proc options
     restrict;
run;
code }

}

